Pretrained policy checkpoints (evaluated in v1)

  The v1 sweep runs pretrained checkpoints mirrored under the `lerobot/*`
  Hugging Face Hub org. Each checkpoint carries an apache-2.0 license tag
  on its Hub card (see docs/MODEL_CARDS.md for repo IDs + locked revision
  SHAs). The benchmark does not redistribute the weights themselves; only
  the per-episode evaluation outcomes and rendered rollouts are published.

  ACT (Action Chunking Transformer)
    Checkpoint: lerobot/act_aloha_sim_transfer_cube_human (apache-2.0)
    Cite: Zhao, Kumar, Levine, Finn, "Learning Fine-Grained Bimanual
    Manipulation with Low-Cost Hardware", RSS 2023 (arXiv:2304.13705).
    The Aloha (ALOHA) hardware/task family originates from the same work.

  Diffusion Policy
    Checkpoint: lerobot/diffusion_pusht (apache-2.0)
    Cite: Chi, Feng, Du, Xu, Cousineau, Burchfiel, Song, "Diffusion
    Policy: Visuomotor Policy Learning via Action Diffusion", RSS 2023
    (arXiv:2303.04137). The PushT task originates from this work.

  SmolVLA
    Checkpoint: lerobot/smolvla_libero (apache-2.0)
    Cite: Shukor, Aubakirova, Capuano, et al., "SmolVLA: A
    Vision-Language-Action Model for Affordable and Efficient Robotics",
    2025 (arXiv:2506.01844).

  The no_op and random baselines have no upstream weights; their
  implementations live in this repository under its MIT license.

